text: Misapata (Quechua misa table, pata elevated place; above, at the top; edge, bank, shore,Yachakuqkunapa Simi Qullqa - Qusqu Qullaw. Qhichwa Simipi (monolingual Quechua and bilingual Quechua-Spanish dictionary) also spelled Mesapata) is a mountain in the Andes of Peru, about high. It is situated in the Ayacucho Region, Lucanas Province, Cabana District. It lies northwest of Anqasi and east of Saywa (Saygua). == References == Category:Mountains of Peru Category:Mountains of Ayacucho Region
title: Misapata (Cabana)
